@page "/"

<PageTitle>2D RPG Engine</PageTitle>

<section class="landing-hero" aria-labelledby="landing-title">
    <p class="eyebrow">Browser-based 2D RPG toolkit</p>
    <h1 id="landing-title">Build classic RPG worlds with a focused engine and a visual editor.</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy">
        The 2D RPG Engine project combines runtime systems for maps, objects, events, and combat with an
        in-browser Blazor editor for authoring playable adventures. Use the tabs below to explore what belongs
        to the engine runtime and what belongs to the editor workspace.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions" role="navigation" aria-label="Project areas">
        <NavLink class="btn btn-primary" href="engine">Explore Engine</NavLink>
        <NavLink class="btn btn-outline-light" href="editor">Open Editor</NavLink>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="landing-tabs" aria-label="2D RPG Engine and Editor overview">
    <NavLink class="landing-tab engine-tab" href="engine">
        <span class="tab-kicker">Engine tab</span>
        <strong>Runtime foundation</strong>
        <span>Tile maps, collision-aware objects, scripted events, and battle-ready gameplay data.</span>
    </NavLink>
    <NavLink class="landing-tab editor-tab" href="editor">
        <span class="tab-kicker">Editor tab</span>
        <strong>Authoring workspace</strong>
        <span>Paint maps, manage layers, place objects and events, and validate project content interactively.</span>
    </NavLink>
</section>
